The '''drink industry''' (also known as the '''beverage industry''') produces [[drink]]s, in particular [[ready to drink]] products. Drink production can vary greatly depending on the product being made. ManufacturingDrinks.com explains that, "bottling facilities differ in the types of [[bottling line]]s they operate and the types of products they can run". Drinks may be [[beverage can|canned]] or [[bottle]]d ([[Plastic bottle|plastic]] or [[glass bottle|glass]]), hot-fill or cold-fill, and natural or conventional. Innovations in the drink industry, catalysed by requests for [[non-alcoholic drink]]s, include: drink plants, drink processing, and drink packing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.manufacturingdrinks.com/Production/BeverageProduction.html |title=Beverage Production |publisher=Manufacturingdrinks.com |date=2010-06-07 |accessdate=2013-05-21}}</ref>
