[[File:Granvia L'H, vist des del cementiri de Montjuic.JPG|thumb|Granvia l'H with [[Fira de Barcelona]] in the centre and the skyscrapers of [[Plaça d'Europa]] behind]]
[[File:Barris de l'Hospitalet.svg|thumb|Granvia L'H marked in green]]
'''Granvia l'Hospitalet''' or '''Granvia l'H''' is a district ("Districte VII") in the municipality of [[L'Hospitalet de Llobregat]], a south-western suburb of the [[Barcelona metropolitan area]].

Part of Granvia L'H is part of [[Gran Via (Barcelona)|Gran Via business center]] of [[Barcelona]] and directly [[Fira de Barcelona]], second largest trade fair and exhibition centres in [[Europe]].

== Public transport ==
The Granvia area is served by line 8 of the [[Barcelona Metro]] and [[Ferrocarrils de la Generalitat de Catalunya|FGC]] commuter train network, at the [[Europa-Fira (Barcelona Metro)|Europa-Fira station]], and also by the bus line 79.

